main event: A silvery disc-shaped object was observed near Mooseheart, Illinois on July 8, 1959.
interesting points: The object was seen at around 8 o'clock, near sunset., The sighting lasted for 30 minutes., The weather was described as scattered clouds but not around the sighting., The observation was made in the general direction of Aurora, Illinois., The report concludes that the object could have been a balloon, celestial, or probably astronomical.
